      (0): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
      (1): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
      (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
    )
    (ppm): PyramidPoolingModuleONNX(
      (stages): ModuleList(
        (0): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(20, 20), stride=(20, 20), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (1): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(10, 10), stride=(10, 10), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (2): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(8, 8), stride=(6, 6), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (3): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(5, 5), stride=(3, 3), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
      )
      (bottleneck): Conv2d(512, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
    (fusion): Conv2d(768, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
  )
  (decoder): GroupIAMDecoder(
    (inst_branch): GroupInstanceBranch(
      (inst_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (iam_conv): Conv2d(256, 400, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1), groups=4)
      (fc): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1024, bias=True)
      (cls_score): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=80, bias=True)
      (mask_kernel): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=128, bias=True)
      (objectness): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1, bias=True)
    )
    (mask_branch): MaskBranch(
      (mask_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (projection): Conv2d(256, 128, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
  )
  (criterion): SparseInstCriterion(
    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )
)

        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (projection): Conv2d(256, 128, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
  )
  (criterion): SparseInstCriterion(
    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )

          512, 2048, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False

        )

          2048, 512, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False

        )
      )
    )

      )

          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(5, 5), stride=(3, 3), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
      )
      (bottleneck): Conv2d(512, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
    (fusion): Conv2d(768, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
  )
  (decoder): GroupIAMDecoder(
    (inst_branch): GroupInstanceBranch(
      (inst_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (iam_conv): Conv2d(256, 400, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1), groups=4)
      (fc): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1024, bias=True)
      (cls_score): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=80, bias=True)
      (mask_kernel): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=128, bias=True)
      (objectness): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1, bias=True)
    )
    (mask_branch): MaskBranch(
      (mask_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (projection): Conv2d(256, 128, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
  )
  (criterion): SparseInstCriterion(
    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )
)

          (norm): BatchNorm2d(2048, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
      )
    )
  )
  (encoder): InstanceContextEncoder(
    (fpn_laterals): ModuleList(
      (0): Conv2d(2048, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
      (1): Conv2d(1024, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
      (2): Conv2d(512, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
    (fpn_outputs): ModuleList(
      (0): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
      (1): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
      (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
    )
    (ppm): PyramidPoolingModuleONNX(
      (stages): ModuleList(
        (0): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(20, 20), stride=(20, 20), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (1): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(10, 10), stride=(10, 10), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (2): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(8, 8), stride=(6, 6), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (3): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(5, 5), stride=(3, 3), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
      )
      (bottleneck): Conv2d(512, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
    (fusion): Conv2d(768, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
  )
  (decoder): GroupIAMDecoder(
    (inst_branch): GroupInstanceBranch(
      (inst_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (iam_conv): Conv2d(256, 400, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1), groups=4)
      (fc): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1024, bias=True)
      (cls_score): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=80, bias=True)
      (mask_kernel): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=128, bias=True)
      (objectness): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1, bias=True)
    )
    (mask_branch): MaskBranch(
      (mask_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (projection): Conv2d(256, 128, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
  )
  (criterion): SparseInstCriterion(
    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )
)

          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (3): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(5, 5), stride=(3, 3), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
      )
      (bottleneck): Conv2d(512, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
    (fusion): Conv2d(768, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
  )
  (decoder): GroupIAMDecoder(
    (inst_branch): GroupInstanceBranch(
      (inst_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (iam_conv): Conv2d(256, 400, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1), groups=4)
      (fc): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1024, bias=True)
      (cls_score): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=80, bias=True)
      (mask_kernel): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=128, bias=True)
      (objectness): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1, bias=True)
    )
    (mask_branch): MaskBranch(
      (mask_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (projection): Conv2d(256, 128, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
  )
  (criterion): SparseInstCriterion(
    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )
)

    (mask_branch): MaskBranch(
      (mask_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (projection): Conv2d(256, 128, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
  )
  (criterion): SparseInstCriterion(
    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )
)

          (norm): BatchNorm2d(128, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
        (conv2): Conv2d(
          128, 128, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(128, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
        (conv3): Conv2d(
          128, 512, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(512, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
      )
    )
    (res4): Sequential(
      (0): BottleneckBlock(
        (shortcut): Conv2d(
          512, 1024, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(2, 2), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(1024, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )

          512, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False

        )
        (conv2): Conv2d(
          256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(2, 2), padding=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(256, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
        (conv3): Conv2d(
          256, 1024, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(1024, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
      )
      (1): BottleneckBlock(
        (conv1): Conv2d(
          1024, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False

        )

        )

        )
        (conv3): Conv2d(
          512, 2048, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(2048, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
      )
    )
  )
  (encoder): InstanceContextEncoder(
    (fpn_laterals): ModuleList(
      (0): Conv2d(2048, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
      (1): Conv2d(1024, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
      (2): Conv2d(512, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
    (fpn_outputs): ModuleList(
      (0): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
      (1): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
      (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
    )
    (ppm): PyramidPoolingModuleONNX(
      (stages): ModuleList(
        (0): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(20, 20), stride=(20, 20), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (1): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(10, 10), stride=(10, 10), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (2): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(8, 8), stride=(6, 6), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (3): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(5, 5), stride=(3, 3), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
      )
      (bottleneck): Conv2d(512, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
    (fusion): Conv2d(768, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
  )
  (decoder): GroupIAMDecoder(
    (inst_branch): GroupInstanceBranch(
      (inst_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (iam_conv): Conv2d(256, 400, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1), groups=4)
      (fc): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1024, bias=True)
      (cls_score): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=80, bias=True)
      (mask_kernel): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=128, bias=True)
      (objectness): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1, bias=True)
    )
    (mask_branch): MaskBranch(
      (mask_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (projection): Conv2d(256, 128, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
  )
  (criterion): SparseInstCriterion(
    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )
)

          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(10, 10), stride=(10, 10), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (2): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(8, 8), stride=(6, 6), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (3): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(5, 5), stride=(3, 3), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
      )
      (bottleneck): Conv2d(512, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
    (fusion): Conv2d(768, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
  )
  (decoder): GroupIAMDecoder(
    (inst_branch): GroupInstanceBranch(
      (inst_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (iam_conv): Conv2d(256, 400, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1), groups=4)
      (fc): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1024, bias=True)
      (cls_score): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=80, bias=True)
      (mask_kernel): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=128, bias=True)
      (objectness): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1, bias=True)
    )
    (mask_branch): MaskBranch(
      (mask_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (projection): Conv2d(256, 128, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
  )
  (criterion): SparseInstCriterion(
    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )
)

      )

    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()

        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )

    )
  )
  (criterion): SparseInstCriterion(
    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )

          512, 1024, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(2, 2), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(1024, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )

        )
        (conv2): Conv2d(
          256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(2, 2), padding=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(256, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
        (conv3): Conv2d(
          256, 1024, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(1024, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
      )
      (1): BottleneckBlock(
        (conv1): Conv2d(
          1024, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False

      (0): BottleneckBlock(
        (shortcut): Conv2d(

        )

          512, 512, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(512, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
        (conv3): Conv2d(
          512, 2048, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(2048, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
      )

        (conv1): Conv2d(
          2048, 512, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False

        )
        (conv2): Conv2d(
          512, 512, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(512, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
        (conv3): Conv2d(
          512, 2048, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(2048, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
      )
    )
  )
  (encoder): InstanceContextEncoder(
    (fpn_laterals): ModuleList(
      (0): Conv2d(2048, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
      (1): Conv2d(1024, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
      (2): Conv2d(512, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
    (fpn_outputs): ModuleList(
      (0): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
      (1): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
      (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
    )
    (ppm): PyramidPoolingModuleONNX(
      (stages): ModuleList(
        (0): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(20, 20), stride=(20, 20), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (1): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(10, 10), stride=(10, 10), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (2): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(8, 8), stride=(6, 6), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (3): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(5, 5), stride=(3, 3), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
      )
      (bottleneck): Conv2d(512, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
    (fusion): Conv2d(768, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
  )
  (decoder): GroupIAMDecoder(
    (inst_branch): GroupInstanceBranch(
      (inst_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (iam_conv): Conv2d(256, 400, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1), groups=4)
      (fc): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1024, bias=True)
      (cls_score): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=80, bias=True)
      (mask_kernel): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=128, bias=True)
      (objectness): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1, bias=True)
    )
    (mask_branch): MaskBranch(
      (mask_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (projection): Conv2d(256, 128, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
  )
  (criterion): SparseInstCriterion(
    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )
)

        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (iam_conv): Conv2d(256, 400, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1), groups=4)
      (fc): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1024, bias=True)
      (cls_score): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=80, bias=True)
      (mask_kernel): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=128, bias=True)
      (objectness): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1, bias=True)
    )
    (mask_branch): MaskBranch(
      (mask_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (projection): Conv2d(256, 128, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
  )
  (criterion): SparseInstCriterion(
    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )
)

        )
      )

          2048, 512, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False

          (norm): BatchNorm2d(2048, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
      )
    )
  )

    (fpn_laterals): ModuleList(
      (0): Conv2d(2048, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
      (1): Conv2d(1024, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
      (2): Conv2d(512, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
    (fpn_outputs): ModuleList(
      (0): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
      (1): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
      (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
    )
    (ppm): PyramidPoolingModuleONNX(
      (stages): ModuleList(
        (0): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(20, 20), stride=(20, 20), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (1): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(10, 10), stride=(10, 10), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (2): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(8, 8), stride=(6, 6), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (3): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(5, 5), stride=(3, 3), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
      )
      (bottleneck): Conv2d(512, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
    (fusion): Conv2d(768, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
  )
  (decoder): GroupIAMDecoder(
    (inst_branch): GroupInstanceBranch(
      (inst_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)

        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (iam_conv): Conv2d(256, 400, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1), groups=4)
      (fc): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1024, bias=True)
      (cls_score): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=80, bias=True)
      (mask_kernel): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=128, bias=True)
      (objectness): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1, bias=True)
    )
    (mask_branch): MaskBranch(
      (mask_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (projection): Conv2d(256, 128, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
  )
  (criterion): SparseInstCriterion(
    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )
)

      (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
    )

        (0): Sequential(

          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (1): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(10, 10), stride=(10, 10), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )

          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(8, 8), stride=(6, 6), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))

          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
      )
      (bottleneck): Conv2d(512, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
    (fusion): Conv2d(768, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
  )
  (decoder): GroupIAMDecoder(
    (inst_branch): GroupInstanceBranch(
      (inst_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))

      (objectness): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1, bias=True)
    )
    (mask_branch): MaskBranch(
      (mask_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)

        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)

        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (projection): Conv2d(256, 128, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
  )
  (criterion): SparseInstCriterion(
    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )

        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )

    )
  )

      (projection): Conv2d(256, 128, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
  )

    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )
)

          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(20, 20), stride=(20, 20), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (1): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(10, 10), stride=(10, 10), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (2): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(8, 8), stride=(6, 6), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (3): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(5, 5), stride=(3, 3), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
      )
      (bottleneck): Conv2d(512, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
    (fusion): Conv2d(768, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
  )
  (decoder): GroupIAMDecoder(
    (inst_branch): GroupInstanceBranch(
      (inst_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (iam_conv): Conv2d(256, 400, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1), groups=4)
      (fc): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1024, bias=True)
      (cls_score): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=80, bias=True)
      (mask_kernel): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=128, bias=True)
      (objectness): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1, bias=True)
    )
    (mask_branch): MaskBranch(
      (mask_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (projection): Conv2d(256, 128, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
  )
  (criterion): SparseInstCriterion(
    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )
)

          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )

          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(10, 10), stride=(10, 10), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))

          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))

      )

    )

  )

    (inst_branch): GroupInstanceBranch(
      (inst_convs): Sequential(

        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)

        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (projection): Conv2d(256, 128, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
  )
  (criterion): SparseInstCriterion(
    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )

        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )

        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (projection): Conv2d(256, 128, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
  )
  (criterion): SparseInstCriterion(
    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )
)

      (2): Conv2d(512, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
    (fpn_outputs): ModuleList(
      (0): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
      (1): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
      (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
    )
    (ppm): PyramidPoolingModuleONNX(
      (stages): ModuleList(
        (0): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(20, 20), stride=(20, 20), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (1): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(10, 10), stride=(10, 10), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (2): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(8, 8), stride=(6, 6), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (3): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(5, 5), stride=(3, 3), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
      )
      (bottleneck): Conv2d(512, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
    (fusion): Conv2d(768, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
  )
  (decoder): GroupIAMDecoder(
    (inst_branch): GroupInstanceBranch(
      (inst_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (iam_conv): Conv2d(256, 400, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1), groups=4)
      (fc): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1024, bias=True)
      (cls_score): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=80, bias=True)
      (mask_kernel): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=128, bias=True)
      (objectness): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1, bias=True)
    )
    (mask_branch): MaskBranch(
      (mask_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (projection): Conv2d(256, 128, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
  )
  (criterion): SparseInstCriterion(
    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )
)

        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )

    )
  )

    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )

        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )

    )
  )

  )

    (inst_branch): GroupInstanceBranch(
      (inst_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (iam_conv): Conv2d(256, 400, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1), groups=4)
      (fc): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1024, bias=True)
      (cls_score): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=80, bias=True)
      (mask_kernel): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=128, bias=True)
      (objectness): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1, bias=True)
    )
    (mask_branch): MaskBranch(
      (mask_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (projection): Conv2d(256, 128, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
  )
  (criterion): SparseInstCriterion(
    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )
)

        )
      )
    )
  )

    (fpn_laterals): ModuleList(

      (2): Conv2d(512, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )

      (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
    )
    (ppm): PyramidPoolingModuleONNX(
      (stages): ModuleList(
        (0): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(20, 20), stride=(20, 20), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (1): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(10, 10), stride=(10, 10), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (2): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(8, 8), stride=(6, 6), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (3): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(5, 5), stride=(3, 3), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
      )
      (bottleneck): Conv2d(512, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
    (fusion): Conv2d(768, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
  )
  (decoder): GroupIAMDecoder(
    (inst_branch): GroupInstanceBranch(
      (inst_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))

        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )

      (fc): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1024, bias=True)
      (cls_score): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=80, bias=True)
      (mask_kernel): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=128, bias=True)
      (objectness): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1, bias=True)
    )
    (mask_branch): MaskBranch(
      (mask_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (projection): Conv2d(256, 128, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
  )
  (criterion): SparseInstCriterion(
    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )
)

      (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
    )

      (stages): ModuleList(
        (0): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(20, 20), stride=(20, 20), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (1): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(10, 10), stride=(10, 10), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )

          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(8, 8), stride=(6, 6), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (3): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(5, 5), stride=(3, 3), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
      )
      (bottleneck): Conv2d(512, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
    (fusion): Conv2d(768, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
  )
  (decoder): GroupIAMDecoder(
    (inst_branch): GroupInstanceBranch(
      (inst_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))

      (mask_kernel): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=128, bias=True)
      (objectness): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1, bias=True)
    )
    (mask_branch): MaskBranch(
      (mask_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (projection): Conv2d(256, 128, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
  )
  (criterion): SparseInstCriterion(
    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )
)

          (norm): BatchNorm2d(1024, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
      )
      (1): BottleneckBlock(
        (conv1): Conv2d(
          1024, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(256, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
        (conv2): Conv2d(
          256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(256, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
        (conv3): Conv2d(
          256, 1024, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(1024, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
      )
      (2): BottleneckBlock(
        (conv1): Conv2d(
          1024, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(256, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
        (conv2): Conv2d(
          256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(256, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
        (conv3): Conv2d(
          256, 1024, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(1024, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
      )
      (3): BottleneckBlock(
        (conv1): Conv2d(
          1024, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False

        (conv2): Conv2d(

        (conv1): Conv2d(
          1024, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False

        )

      )
      (5): BottleneckBlock(
        (conv1): Conv2d(
          1024, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False

        )
        (conv2): Conv2d(

          (norm): BatchNorm2d(1024, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
      )
    )
    (res5): Sequential(
      (0): BottleneckBlock(
        (shortcut): Conv2d(
          1024, 2048, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(2, 2), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(2048, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
        (conv1): Conv2d(
          1024, 512, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(512, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
        (conv2): Conv2d(
          512, 512, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(2, 2), padding=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(512, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
        (conv3): Conv2d(
          512, 2048, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(2048, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
      )
      (1): BottleneckBlock(
        (conv1): Conv2d(
          2048, 512, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(512, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
        (conv2): Conv2d(
          512, 512, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(512, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
        (conv3): Conv2d(
          512, 2048, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(2048, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
      )
      (2): BottleneckBlock(
        (conv1): Conv2d(
          2048, 512, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(512, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
        (conv2): Conv2d(
          512, 512, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(512, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
        (conv3): Conv2d(
          512, 2048, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(2048, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
      )
    )
  )
  (encoder): InstanceContextEncoder(
    (fpn_laterals): ModuleList(
      (0): Conv2d(2048, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
      (1): Conv2d(1024, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
      (2): Conv2d(512, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
    (fpn_outputs): ModuleList(
      (0): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
      (1): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
      (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
    )
    (ppm): PyramidPoolingModuleONNX(
      (stages): ModuleList(
        (0): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(20, 20), stride=(20, 20), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (1): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(10, 10), stride=(10, 10), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (2): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(8, 8), stride=(6, 6), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (3): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(5, 5), stride=(3, 3), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
      )
      (bottleneck): Conv2d(512, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
    (fusion): Conv2d(768, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
  )
  (decoder): GroupIAMDecoder(
    (inst_branch): GroupInstanceBranch(
      (inst_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (iam_conv): Conv2d(256, 400, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1), groups=4)
      (fc): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1024, bias=True)
      (cls_score): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=80, bias=True)
      (mask_kernel): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=128, bias=True)
      (objectness): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1, bias=True)
    )
    (mask_branch): MaskBranch(
      (mask_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (projection): Conv2d(256, 128, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
  )
  (criterion): SparseInstCriterion(
    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )
)

      (fc): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1024, bias=True)
      (cls_score): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=80, bias=True)
      (mask_kernel): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=128, bias=True)
      (objectness): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1, bias=True)
    )
    (mask_branch): MaskBranch(
      (mask_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (projection): Conv2d(256, 128, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
  )
  (criterion): SparseInstCriterion(
    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )
)

          512, 2048, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(2048, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
      )
    )
  )
  (encoder): InstanceContextEncoder(
    (fpn_laterals): ModuleList(
      (0): Conv2d(2048, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
      (1): Conv2d(1024, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
      (2): Conv2d(512, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
    (fpn_outputs): ModuleList(
      (0): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
      (1): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
      (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
    )
    (ppm): PyramidPoolingModuleONNX(
      (stages): ModuleList(
        (0): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(20, 20), stride=(20, 20), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (1): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(10, 10), stride=(10, 10), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (2): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(8, 8), stride=(6, 6), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (3): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(5, 5), stride=(3, 3), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
      )
      (bottleneck): Conv2d(512, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
    (fusion): Conv2d(768, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
  )
  (decoder): GroupIAMDecoder(
    (inst_branch): GroupInstanceBranch(
      (inst_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (iam_conv): Conv2d(256, 400, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1), groups=4)
      (fc): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1024, bias=True)
      (cls_score): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=80, bias=True)
      (mask_kernel): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=128, bias=True)
      (objectness): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1, bias=True)
    )
    (mask_branch): MaskBranch(
      (mask_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (projection): Conv2d(256, 128, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
  )
  (criterion): SparseInstCriterion(
    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )
)

        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (projection): Conv2d(256, 128, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
  )
  (criterion): SparseInstCriterion(
    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )

          (norm): BatchNorm2d(256, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
        (conv3): Conv2d(
          256, 1024, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(1024, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
      )
      (2): BottleneckBlock(
        (conv1): Conv2d(
          1024, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(256, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
        (conv2): Conv2d(
          256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(256, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
        (conv3): Conv2d(
          256, 1024, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(1024, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
      )
      (3): BottleneckBlock(
        (conv1): Conv2d(
          1024, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(256, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
        (conv2): Conv2d(
          256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(256, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
        (conv3): Conv2d(
          256, 1024, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(1024, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
      )
      (4): BottleneckBlock(
        (conv1): Conv2d(
          1024, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(256, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
        (conv2): Conv2d(
          256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(256, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
        (conv3): Conv2d(
          256, 1024, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(1024, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
      )
      (5): BottleneckBlock(
        (conv1): Conv2d(
          1024, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(256, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
        (conv2): Conv2d(
          256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(256, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
        (conv3): Conv2d(
          256, 1024, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(1024, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
      )
    )
    (res5): Sequential(
      (0): BottleneckBlock(
        (shortcut): Conv2d(
          1024, 2048, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(2, 2), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(2048, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
        (conv1): Conv2d(
          1024, 512, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(512, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
        (conv2): Conv2d(
          512, 512, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(2, 2), padding=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(512, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
        (conv3): Conv2d(
          512, 2048, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(2048, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
      )
      (1): BottleneckBlock(
        (conv1): Conv2d(
          2048, 512, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(512, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
        (conv2): Conv2d(
          512, 512, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(512, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
        (conv3): Conv2d(
          512, 2048, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(2048, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
      )
      (2): BottleneckBlock(
        (conv1): Conv2d(
          2048, 512, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(512, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
        (conv2): Conv2d(
          512, 512, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(512, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
        (conv3): Conv2d(
          512, 2048, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(2048, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
      )
    )
  )
  (encoder): InstanceContextEncoder(
    (fpn_laterals): ModuleList(
      (0): Conv2d(2048, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
      (1): Conv2d(1024, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
      (2): Conv2d(512, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
    (fpn_outputs): ModuleList(
      (0): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
      (1): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
      (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
    )
    (ppm): PyramidPoolingModuleONNX(
      (stages): ModuleList(
        (0): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(20, 20), stride=(20, 20), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (1): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(10, 10), stride=(10, 10), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (2): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(8, 8), stride=(6, 6), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (3): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(5, 5), stride=(3, 3), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
      )
      (bottleneck): Conv2d(512, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
    (fusion): Conv2d(768, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
  )
  (decoder): GroupIAMDecoder(
    (inst_branch): GroupInstanceBranch(
      (inst_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (iam_conv): Conv2d(256, 400, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1), groups=4)
      (fc): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1024, bias=True)
      (cls_score): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=80, bias=True)
      (mask_kernel): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=128, bias=True)
      (objectness): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1, bias=True)
    )
    (mask_branch): MaskBranch(
      (mask_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (projection): Conv2d(256, 128, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
  )
  (criterion): SparseInstCriterion(
    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )
)

        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (projection): Conv2d(256, 128, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
  )

    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )

      (2): Conv2d(512, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
    (fpn_outputs): ModuleList(
      (0): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
      (1): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
      (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
    )
    (ppm): PyramidPoolingModuleONNX(
      (stages): ModuleList(
        (0): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(20, 20), stride=(20, 20), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (1): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(10, 10), stride=(10, 10), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (2): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(8, 8), stride=(6, 6), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (3): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(5, 5), stride=(3, 3), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
      )
      (bottleneck): Conv2d(512, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
    (fusion): Conv2d(768, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
  )
  (decoder): GroupIAMDecoder(
    (inst_branch): GroupInstanceBranch(
      (inst_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (iam_conv): Conv2d(256, 400, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1), groups=4)
      (fc): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1024, bias=True)
      (cls_score): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=80, bias=True)
      (mask_kernel): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=128, bias=True)
      (objectness): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1, bias=True)
    )
    (mask_branch): MaskBranch(
      (mask_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (projection): Conv2d(256, 128, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
  )
  (criterion): SparseInstCriterion(
    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )
)

          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )

          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(10, 10), stride=(10, 10), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))

    )

  )
  (decoder): GroupIAMDecoder(
    (inst_branch): GroupInstanceBranch(
      (inst_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)

        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (projection): Conv2d(256, 128, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
  )
  (criterion): SparseInstCriterion(
    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )

        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (projection): Conv2d(256, 128, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
  )

    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )

          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (3): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(5, 5), stride=(3, 3), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
      )
      (bottleneck): Conv2d(512, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
    (fusion): Conv2d(768, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
  )
  (decoder): GroupIAMDecoder(
    (inst_branch): GroupInstanceBranch(
      (inst_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (iam_conv): Conv2d(256, 400, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1), groups=4)
      (fc): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1024, bias=True)
      (cls_score): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=80, bias=True)
      (mask_kernel): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=128, bias=True)
      (objectness): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1, bias=True)
    )
    (mask_branch): MaskBranch(
      (mask_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (projection): Conv2d(256, 128, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
  )
  (criterion): SparseInstCriterion(
    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )
)

      (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
    )

        (0): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(20, 20), stride=(20, 20), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )

          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(10, 10), stride=(10, 10), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )

          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(8, 8), stride=(6, 6), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )

          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
      )
      (bottleneck): Conv2d(512, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
    (fusion): Conv2d(768, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
  )
  (decoder): GroupIAMDecoder(
    (inst_branch): GroupInstanceBranch(
      (inst_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))

    )

      (mask_convs): Sequential(

        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)

        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (projection): Conv2d(256, 128, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
  )
  (criterion): SparseInstCriterion(
    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )

        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )

    )
  )

    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )

        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (projection): Conv2d(256, 128, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
  )

    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )

      (2): Conv2d(512, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
    (fpn_outputs): ModuleList(
      (0): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
      (1): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
      (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
    )
    (ppm): PyramidPoolingModuleONNX(
      (stages): ModuleList(
        (0): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(20, 20), stride=(20, 20), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (1): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(10, 10), stride=(10, 10), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (2): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(8, 8), stride=(6, 6), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (3): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(5, 5), stride=(3, 3), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
      )
      (bottleneck): Conv2d(512, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
    (fusion): Conv2d(768, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
  )
  (decoder): GroupIAMDecoder(
    (inst_branch): GroupInstanceBranch(
      (inst_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (iam_conv): Conv2d(256, 400, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1), groups=4)
      (fc): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1024, bias=True)
      (cls_score): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=80, bias=True)
      (mask_kernel): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=128, bias=True)
      (objectness): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1, bias=True)
    )
    (mask_branch): MaskBranch(
      (mask_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (projection): Conv2d(256, 128, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
  )
  (criterion): SparseInstCriterion(
    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )
)

        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )

    )
  )

    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )

        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )

    )
  )

    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )

        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (iam_conv): Conv2d(256, 400, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1), groups=4)
      (fc): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1024, bias=True)
      (cls_score): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=80, bias=True)
      (mask_kernel): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=128, bias=True)
      (objectness): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1, bias=True)
    )
    (mask_branch): MaskBranch(
      (mask_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (projection): Conv2d(256, 128, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
  )
  (criterion): SparseInstCriterion(
    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )
)

          512, 2048, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(2048, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
      )

        (conv1): Conv2d(
          2048, 512, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(512, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )

          512, 2048, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1), bias=False
          (norm): BatchNorm2d(2048, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
        )
      )
    )
  )
  (encoder): InstanceContextEncoder(
    (fpn_laterals): ModuleList(
      (0): Conv2d(2048, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
      (1): Conv2d(1024, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
      (2): Conv2d(512, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
    (fpn_outputs): ModuleList(
      (0): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
      (1): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
      (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
    )
    (ppm): PyramidPoolingModuleONNX(
      (stages): ModuleList(
        (0): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(20, 20), stride=(20, 20), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (1): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(10, 10), stride=(10, 10), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (2): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(8, 8), stride=(6, 6), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
        (3): Sequential(
          (0): AvgPool2d(kernel_size=(5, 5), stride=(3, 3), padding=0)
          (1): Conv2d(256, 64, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
        )
      )
      (bottleneck): Conv2d(512, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
    (fusion): Conv2d(768, 256, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
  )
  (decoder): GroupIAMDecoder(
    (inst_branch): GroupInstanceBranch(
      (inst_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (iam_conv): Conv2d(256, 400, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1), groups=4)
      (fc): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1024, bias=True)
      (cls_score): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=80, bias=True)
      (mask_kernel): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=128, bias=True)
      (objectness): Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=1, bias=True)
    )
    (mask_branch): MaskBranch(
      (mask_convs): Sequential(
        (0): Conv2d(258, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (1): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (2): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (3): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (4): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (5): ReLU(inplace=True)
        (6): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
        (7): ReLU(inplace=True)
      )
      (projection): Conv2d(256, 128, kernel_size=(1, 1), stride=(1, 1))
    )
  )
  (criterion): SparseInstCriterion(
    (matcher): SparseInstMatcher()
  )
)

    )
